FuncDef: The access https-redirect delete certificate command deletes the imported certificate and key.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
In the HTTPS redirection scenario, if the imported certificate and private key have been imported using the access https-redirect import certificate command and you need to use the signature certificate to interact with the client using HTTPS, run the self-signed rsa modulus command to generate the signature certificate and then run this command to delete the imported certificate and private key.
Prerequisites
The externally generated certificate and the mapped key have been imported using the access https-redirect import certificate command.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
